ALGORITHM
Main Algorithm (Program Flow)
Start
Display menu:
Add Book
Display All Books
Search Book
Delete Book
Issue Book
Return Book
Exit
Read user choice
Perform operation based on choice:
If 1 → Add Book
If 2 → Display Books
If 3 → Search Book
If 4 → Delete Book
If 5 → Issue Book
If 6 → Return Book
If 0 → Exit
Repeat steps 2–4 until user chooses Exit
End
📘 Sub-Algorithms
1. Add Book
Create Book object
Input Book ID, Title, Author
Set issued = false
Open file (library.dat) in append mode
Write object into file
Close file
2. Display All Books
Open file in read mode
If file not found → show message
Read each record
Display book details
Close file
3. Search Book
Input Book ID
Open file
Read records one by one
If ID matches → display book
If not found → show message
Close file
4. Delete Book
Input Book ID
Open original file (read mode)
Open temporary file (write mode)
Copy all records except matching ID
Close files
Delete original file
Rename temp file to original
Display result
5. Issue Book
Input Book ID
Open file in read/write mode
Search record
If found and not issued:
Mark as issued
Rewrite record in same position
Else show error
Close file
6. Return Book
Input Book ID
Open file in read/write mode
Search record
If found and issued:
Mark as returned
Rewrite record
Else show error
Close file
